jQuery Clusting Plugin - By Vangelis Tsoumenis
===================================================================


This plugin takes a List (i.e an unordered List) with positioned (via css) elements and clusters them by proximity.

This is way alpha!

Usage 
------------------------------------------------------------------


HTML:

<ul id="mymap"> 
  <li style="left:1.2em; top:1emi;">Marker 1</li>
  <li style="left:0.3em; top:1.4em;">Marker 2</li>
  <li style="left:2.3em; top:1.7em;">Marker 3</li>
</ul> 

CSS:

ul#mymap {
  position:relative; 
} 

ul#mymap li {
  position:absolute;
}

JAVASCRIPT: 

$(document).ready(function(){
  $('ul#mymap').cluster();
});


Options: 
------------------------------------------------------------------
  * radius (2.3) 
  Max. proximity of a marker to a clusters center to be included in the cluster.

  * distance_func 
  The function to calculate the distance between two objects.
  
  * marker_image 
  image src for a marker

  * repesentation

  .... a lot missing here ... 


How to alter the appearance of bunches on the Map?
-------------------------------------------------------------------

The bunches are positioned by jquery-clustering. The positioned Dom-Nodes (usually <li>s) don't contain style information apart from position. 

To control the representation of a bunch functions that act on the Dom-Node will be called by jquery-clustering.  Each function will be passed the dom-node representing the bunch as the first argument and the actuall bunch object as the second argument. 
The functions that are called are the ones in the array $.fn.clusters.default.representation. 

There are a couple of representation-functions in $.fn.clusters.bunchfuncs
Put them into $.fn.clusters.default.representation like in the demo to try them out.




